<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFFFFC0FF71FBB0FE7CF9A7" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FBB0FCB6FBD2" blockId="23.[151,1437,1086,1292]" box="[151,843,1122,1149]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFFFFC0FF79FBB0FF14FBD2" box="[159,233,1122,1148]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,189,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-32@56.[184,1404,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xylophylla, Gloriana, Huebnerius and Eudocima formosa adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605500/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs 3</figureCitation>
: G–H, 17: J, 22: P–T, 29: I, 71: F, 72: F, 73–77, 88: C)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FB54FF1CFAA2" blockId="23.[151,1437,1086,1292]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFFFFC0FF34FB54FEA4FB0E" box="[210,345,1158,1184]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
endemic is the only species classified as 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FCDCFB54FC51FB0E" box="[826,940,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FCDCFB54FC51FB0E" box="[826,940,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that completely lacks a hindwing marginal band. The medial patch is reduced to a somewhat round dot, a condition otherwise found only in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FB11FB79FAB7FB6A" authorityName="Ophideres" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1271,1354,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apta">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FB11FB79FAB7FB6A" box="[1271,1354,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. apta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FA62FB79FF09FB46" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="materna">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FA62FB79FF09FB46" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. materna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FE9DFB1CFE09FB46" box="[379,500,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FE9DFB1CFE0DFB46" box="[379,496,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eudocima</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The erroneous generic placement is discussed in the 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FBB8FB1CFB3FFB46" box="[1118,1218,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Calpinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Calpinae</taxonomicName>
Phylogeny section below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FAE9FD96FAFA" blockId="23.[151,1437,1338,1545]" box="[151,619,1338,1365]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
[
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FF47FAE8FE31FAFB" bold="true" box="[161,460,1338,1365]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FF47FAE8FEF2FAFB" box="[161,271,1338,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phalaena</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FEC7FAE8FE8FFAFA" box="[289,370,1338,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Noctua" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Noctua</taxonomicName>
] felicia
</emphasis>
] 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FE3DFAE8FD96FAFA" bold="true" box="[475,619,1338,1364]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFFFFC0FE05FAE8FD9FFAFA" author="Stoll, C." box="[483,610,1338,1364]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="43 - 184" refId="ref40628" refString="Stoll, C. (1790) s. n. In: Aahangsel van het Werk, de Uitlandsche Kapellen, Voorkomende in Drie Waereld-Deelen Asia, Africa, en America. Chez Nic. Th. Gravius, Amsterdam, pp. 43 - 184." type="book chapter" year="1790">Stoll, 1790</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FA8CFEE1FAD6" blockId="23.[151,1437,1338,1545]" box="[151,284,1374,1400]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFFFFC0FF46FA8CFF09FAD6" box="[160,244,1374,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="81.[151,250,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,188,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-19@81.[189,1399,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="81" captionText="FIGURE 28. A–O: Eudocima phalonia group and Calpini adults (dorsal aspect); P: Page 41, Plate 310, Figure A from Cramer (1782); Q: Page 58, Plate 12, Figure 11 from Stoll (1790)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605590/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
: Q)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFFFFC0FF71FA50FE7CF9A7" blockId="23.[151,1437,1338,1545]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This unrecognized phenotype from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFFFFC0FDD6FA50FD66FA32" box="[560,667,1410,1436]" name="Suriname" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Suriname</collectingCountry>
was listed as a 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FCB3FA50FC3AFA32" box="[853,967,1410,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FCB3FA50FC3AFA32" box="[853,967,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Poole (1989) and 
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFFFFC0FB25FA50FF18FA6E" author="Zaspel, J. M. &amp; Branham M. A." pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref41518" refString="Zaspel, J. M. &amp; Branham M. A. (2008) World Checklist of Tribe Calpini (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae: Calpinae). Insecta Mundi, 47, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="2008">Zaspel &amp; Branham (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFFFFC0FF17FA74FE03FA6E" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." box="[241,510,1446,1473]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes (2002)</bibRefCitation>
noted the pattern was totally unlike any 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FC37FA74FB61FA6E" box="[977,1180,1446,1472]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FC37FA74FBBEFA6E" box="[977,1091,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
and concluded it does not belong in this group. We agree with the latter interpretation and believe this species should be excluded from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFFFFC0FEEFFA3CFE86F9A6" box="[265,379,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFFFFC0FEEFFA3CFE86F9A6" box="[265,379,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eudocima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
